    "htmlTextContent": "Norse - Valhalla ‚öîÔ∏è Valhalla Home ‚Üí Norse ‚Üí Realms ‚Üí Valhalla Valhalla - Hall of the Slain Odin 's great hall in Asgard where fallen warriors feast and train for Ragnarok . The ultimate destination for those who die heroically in battle. The Hall of Heroes Valhalla (\" hall of the slain \") stands in Asgard with 540 doors, each wide enough for 800 warriors to march through abreast. Its rafters are spears, its roof is shields, and its benches are strewn with armor. Here dwell the Einherjar - warriors chosen by Odin 's Valkyries from among the battle-dead. Each day the Einherjar fight and kill each other in combat training; each evening their wounds heal and they feast on endless meat from the boar Saehrimnir and mead from the goat Heidrun, served by the Valkyries. This is not heaven but Odin 's army, gathered for the final battle at Ragnarok . üîó Related Across the Mythos Archetype ‚öîÔ∏è WARRIOR PARADISE Valhalla represents the ultimate reward for warriors - eternal glory, endless feasting, and battle among the honored dead. See parallels: Elysium, Aaru, Heaven ‚Üí Within Norse Mythology üëÅÔ∏è Odin - Lord of Valhalla ‚öîÔ∏è Valkyries - Choosers of the Slain üî• Ragnarok - The Final Battle üåç Cross-Cultural Parallels üèõÔ∏è Elysium Greek üè∫ Field of Reeds Egyptian ‚úùÔ∏è Heaven Christian ‚òòÔ∏è Otherworld Celtic üìö See Also üíÄ Helheim ‚ö∞Ô∏è Norse Afterlife üó°Ô∏è Norse Heroes üå≥ Yggdrasil Valhalla - Norse Mythology World Mythos Home | Norse Tradition &times; Login to Your Account Username Password Login Don't have an account? Sign up Username Email Password Create Account Already have an account? Login Login Sign Up ‚ñº My Theories Profile Settings Logout // Auth form handlers function handleLogin(event) { event.preventDefault(); const formData = new FormData(event.target); const username = formData.get('username'); const password = formData.get('password'); const result = window.userAuth.login(username, password); 